          <div property="content:encoded" class="field-item even"><p>Part 2 of a 2-part conversation with <a href="/about-us/team/angela-byron">Angie Byron</a> in front of the cameras at NYC Camp 2014, held at United Nations headquarters in New York. In this part of our conversation, we talk about improvements in the Drupal developer- and learning-experience thanks to the major changes under the hood in Drupal 8; the "PHP Renaissance"; and about being welcomed "back into the fold" of the greater PHP world thanks to the nature of Drupal 8 being a sort of "meta project" (my words) that includes parts of many others.</p>
